", description: "The best Dom since 2002. A vintage with very restrained, powerful style that has been released non-sequentially after the 2009. This has a lighter stamp of highly curated, autolytic, toasty aromas than many recent releases. Instead, this delivers super fresh and intense aromas of lemons, grapefruit and blood-orange peel. Incredible freshness here. The palate has a very smoothly delivered, berry-pastry thread with light, sweet spices, stone fruit and fine citrus fruit. This really delivers. Drink now or hold.", score: 95, price: 190, country: "France", region: "Champagne", img_url:"https://www.wine.com/product/images/w_1920,h_2088,c_fit,q_auto:good,fl_progressive/cklazsbjr2hlyrbem4px.jpg")

